Homa Bay county government says it is ready for the construction of a Sh3.8 billion ultramodern hospital. Governor Cyprian Awiti yesterday said they have identifi ed land for the construction. The facility, to be built by the Turkish government, will be constructed near the Homa Bay County Referral Hospital. Speaking in office, Awiti said the ground-breaking ceremony for the construction will be held next month. “We’ve identified land which will be leased for 30 years,” Awiti said. The 210 -bed hospital will handle only complicated cases. On Monday last week, Awiti signed an MoU with the Turkish firm, Delta Trade Company to undertake the construction.